    date: "2026-03-31",
    slug: "the-light-in-the-middle",
    excerpt: `There's a place on Pier 15 in San Francisco called the Exploratorium. My wife and I planned the trip on our fifth anniversary; we'd read about it before we even left Utah. Somewhere inside is an exhibit called the Tactile Dome, a large sphere with a tunnel winding through it, designed to simulate navigating the world without sight. No handrails. No floor lighting. No visible exit. I knew all of this going in. I went in anyway.\n\nI don't love closed spaces. I don't love the dark. I grew up camping with my family and I still remember waking up inside a tent as a kid, opening my eyes and seeing absolutely nothing. The specific, frozen panic that comes when you can't tell if your eyes are open or closed. I never fully outgrew that.\n\nSo naturally, I crawled into the Tactile Dome.`,
